The paper is about the use of artificial intelligence to address societal issues and improve the well-being of the world, which falls under the domain of AI. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the ethical and social implications of AI, which could fall under cs.CY (computers and society) and cs.CR (security and privacy). The paper also proposes conceptual methods to group the existing literature, which could fall under cs.SI (social and information networks). Finally, the paper discusses common challenges in AI4SG, which could fall under cs.LG (machine learning).
